When testing email validation you must think in layers:

Layer 1: structured
has one @
Has domain
Domain has a dots

Layer 2: Character rules
Allowed characters in local part
Allowed characters in domain
Dot placement rules
No spaces

Layer 3: Boundary Conditions
Minimum length
Maximum length
Max local part length (64 chars technically)
Max total length (254 chars technically)

Layer 4: Business Rules
Duplicate emails
Verification required
Disposable emails blocked
Company domain only

Layer 5: Security
Injection attempts
Script tags
SQL payloads


